16x2 LCD                1     LM016L          13.49	 325-375	 Farnell    =
	1     =20

This LCD is 100% compatible except for pinout orientation. I used some =
ribbon cable to get it
working at first and then made a simple pcb adapter wich works fine.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
----------------------
microproc (crystal)     1     8 MHz   	       0.86	 657-606	 R.S     	1=09

This works fine but was a little bit taller than i expected so i have =
had to insulate the top
as the bottom of the lcd rested on it. i will swap this when i get =
around to it.=20
-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
----------------------
8 cell AA nicad pack    1        (local TOYS 'R' US   R/C Section)

I picked this up at toys R us for about 7 pounds=20
-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
----------------------
trimpot                 1        20K (Can only find preset pot types)

I could not find this anywhere. They was all preset types adjusted by =
pot-tweekers.
iam using a multi turn preset pot at the moment as i don't really use it =
yet.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
----------------------
piezo beeper PKM17EPP-4001       (not bothered)       1=B795      =
172-7289	 r.s		5

I found this hard to track down just because most of the catalogs did =
not provide dimensions
of pinout spacing and component size, but after i had ordered all my =
bits i found one in an old=20
R.S book. You may want to double check this is indeed the correct =
part!!!!
-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
-----------------------
Telephone style adapter/charger lead

I had a couple of old phones at work which i hacked the leads off and =
soldered them together
to make the charger/downloader cable
-------------------------------------------------------------------------=
-----------------------

Also one last note.
-------------------
One of the 1K resistor packs where wrong when i came to fit them. I Cant =
remember off hand which
one it was but i ordered all commoned supply type when one of them =
should have been individual 1k
resitors. I got round this by using my left over 1k resistors.

Apart from the few notes above my board took 2 evenings to build and =
worked perfectly.....
                          
